02/04/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana made a one-day official visit to Moldova on Tuesday (1 April).
He announced afterwards that Romania has offered to help its neighbour expand its relations with the EU and with countries in the Black Sea zone.
His delegation discussed trade co-operation issues and the repayment of $37m which Moldova owes to Romania.
(Nine O'Clock, Rompres - 02/04/03)
